Problem Statement 1

Each year, thousands of foreign workers apply for work visas in their quest to work for American companies that are looking to fill gaps in their workforce. In 2013, there were 50,000 work visa applications and of those, 12% were denied, meaning that 6,000 visa cases were denied. Although there has been a Year over Year decrease in denied visa cases over the five-year period between 2010 -2014, the denials are still high in some states and increasing in others.


Click the link below to learn more on foreign workers' impact on  the US economy. 

https://www.americanactionforum.org/research/economic-impact-state-sponsored-work-visas/
